    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our clear offensive anchor. Despite his projected #8 spot, his 82.12 score is fueled by a massive matchup advantage against Chase Petty, who carries an inflated 6.57 xERA; this exploitable arm, combined with favorable wind conditions and a strong platoon split, makes him our premier start. Joining him at the top of the board is **Trea Turner** (65.20) and **Junior Caminero** (65.79). **Trea Turner** remains the engine of our speed-dependent strategy, and while he faces a decent arm in Junk, his leadoff placement maximizes his opportunities to pad our SB and R counts. **Junior Caminero** also gains significant value against Lauer, as his high-skill profile continues to provide consistent production from the #2 slot.\n\nOur most difficult lineup decision today involved **Luke Raley** and his 54.46 score; he was our closest \"bubble\" player to the starting unit but ultimately fell behind due to the defensive and positional requirements of our outfield depth. While **Luke Raley** offers solid upside, the combination of **Carson Benge**'s superior park factor and the platoon advantages granted to **Yordan Alvarez** and **Kyle Schwarber** proved too strong to displace. However, we are monitoring the 34% rain risk surrounding **Carson Benge** closely; should that game be scrubbed, **Luke Raley** is the immediate pivot to ensure we don\u2019t lose plate appearances.\n\nWe are entering today with a cautious eye on lineup volatility, as nearly every one of our starters\u2014specifically **Gary Sanchez**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Kyle Schwarber**, and **Yordan Alvarez**\u2014is subject to pending official lineup confirmation. While we have projected their batting positions based on historical data, any significant drop in the order for **Yordan Alvarez** or **Kyle Schwarber** would marginally dampen their efficiency scores. Furthermore, while we rely on **Hyeseong Kim** for his 41.69 score and sneaky stolen base potential against an admittedly difficult matchup, his value remains tied strictly to his utility in our scarcity-focused build. We remain without the services of **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** due to IL stints, and we continue to await developmental progress from **Zac Veen**, **Josh Smith**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena**, who remain off the active daily board.",
